The paper deals with the security of deep learning systems against Trojan attacks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves analyzing and sanitizing inputs to deep neural networks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of detecting Trojan attacks at runtime, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
